# Spring Container

## Inversion of Control

IOC means giving your designed objects to the spring container control instead of the traditional direct control inside your object.

## Dependency Injection

Dependency : dependent spring container.

Injection: The spring container injects the required object

# Basic useful annotation

## @Qualifier

@Qualifier: If tow class implements one interface, we need to use qualifier to distinguish them.

```java
	@Autowired
    @Qualifier("happyFortune")
    private HappyFortune happyFortune;

    @Autowired
    @Qualifier("randomFortune")
    private RandomFortune randomFortune;
```

## @PostConstruct

@PostConstruct: define initial method, only execute once.

```java
@PostConstruct
    public void doMyStartupStuff() {
        System.out.println("we call the init method");
    }
```

## @InitBinder

@InitBinder: pre-process all web requests coming into this Controller

```java
@InitBinder
    // add an initbinder to convert trim input string
    public void initBinder(WebDataBinder dataBinder) {
        StringTrimmerEditor stringTrimmerEditor = new StringTrimmerEditor(true);
        dataBinder.registerCustomEditor(String.class, stringTrimmerEditor);
    }
```

